Cauliflower Pepper Fry :

🍀In a pan,heat a ts of butter & temper it with a ts of fennel seeds.Add in 2 roughly chopped onions to saute
🍀Add along 2 to 3 ts of pepper powder,pinch of turmeric powder,1/4 cup of coconut paste & required salt to saute along
🍀Add in a bowl of boiled/steamed Cauliflower.Mix them gently & cook for another 5 mins 
🍀 Garnish with 2 to 3 crushed red chillies & curry leaves
And it's done ✅

Very Simple Yogurt Mutton Masala : 
Yogurt always gives you a wonderful taste & texture to any kind of meat & best with mutton .Also we can happily skip the tomatoe🫣wat say ..?? So how much is the price now in your places then ..??? 😂
Here is the recipe :
🍀 Pressure cook 1/2 kg Mutton with a pinch of turmeric powder,ts of salt , a ts of ginger garlic paste,2 red or green chillies & 2 cups of water for about 7 to 8 whistles in med flame
🍀In a pan,heat a spoon of ghee/coconut oil,temper it with a piece of cinnamon stick & 2 cloves
🍀Add in 2 roughly chopped onions & a ts of gg paste to saute 
🍀 Meanwhile,make a fine paste of each 1/4 ts of saunf,pepper & cumin seeds along with 10 to 12 shallots,1/2 ts turmeric powder,2 to 3 ts chilli powder,2 ts coriander powder,2 spoons yogurt & required salt 
🍀Add the masala paste to saute a while & then add in the pressure cooked mutton.Mix gently with 2 ts of coconut paste and cook for another 5 to 6 mins
🍀Garnish with curry leaves & coriander leaves & it's done ✅

Simple Salad with all time local vegetables like pumpkin & Chayote :
Pumpkin has always been my favourite which is bit sweet and I feel it's best for salads 😋.I had few left over mildly roasted paneer from my kids lunch boxes 😛All together went into my bowl 🫣So here it is .. 
.
.
🍀Steam pumpkin & Chayote(may be around 150gms together) with a ts of salt for around 10 to 12 mins 
🍀 Mildly roast a small bowl of paneer(10 to 15 small pieces) in a ts of butter & keep it aside 
🍀In a bowl,Add in the veggies,paneer,10 to 12 overnight soaked almonds 
🍀Now flavour in with a ts of lemon juice,ts of mixed roasted cumin & red chilli powder (add according to your taste bud) .Garnish with mint & coriander leaves
🍀Give a gentle mix & it's done

I used to make this red chilli paste n store them at times.May be with different variations like adding garlic or shallots etc.But this is one of the best versions for stir fries .It always gives that hot n spicy taste to whatever we add them to,even in veggies like sweet potato..It will be top notch 😋👌 #nosauceneeded

South Indian Style Red Chilli Mushroom Stir Fry here.I really thought of adding a good handful of curry leaves rather than spring onions to them n it's my bad ,I don't have at this time.Add them if you have it ll b too good 😊
Spring onions are good too in it's own way😛😎 Try it out n let me know how do you like them and 🤗
.
Recipe here : 
🍀 Heat some water in a bowl and add in 10 to 12 red chillies.Once it gets boiling.Switch off,close n let it sit for around 30 mins .Then make a fine paste n keep it aside
🍀Heat a pan,add a spoon of butter.Add in the 2 ts of chilli paste,salt, n some handful of spring onions(shallots) one by one to stir
🍀Now add in 100gms of roughly chopped clean Mushrooms to stir along for few mins.Add a ts of butter if needed 
🍀Garnish with some spring onions and it's done ✅

This is the kind of Aviyal we used to make at home during Pongal times n Am literally used to its mild n soothing taste. You can also add a cup of yoghurt at last if you wish 🤗 

Just to keep my meal simple,I started adding Paneer to it n everyone loves it here.Also one big bowl of it will keep you full and it's one of the best & rich in fibre,protein, vitamins n the list goes on 😛

Recipe here :
Paneer Aviyal :
☘️ In an open pot.Add in one big bowl of roughly chopped vegetables ,water just below the veggies,2 to 3 ts of salt &1 ts turmeric powder.Close n cook in medium flame for around 15 to 16 mins
☘️ Once the veggies absorbed water n when look soft.Add in a paste of 1/4 cup coconut,1 ts cumin seed & 4 green chillies
☘️Mix it up gently & add along 50 GM's of Paneer .Close n cook for another 3 to 4 mins
☘️Heat a Spoon of coconut oil & temper it with a ts of cumin seeds,2 ts of mustard seeds & few curry leaves
☘️And it's done ✅
.
.
Note : 
☘️ You can also Pressure cook the veggies for a whistle instead of open pot
☘️ Avoid adding up starchy veggies during weight loss period

Egg Series : Recipe 11

Amma used to make this Egg Kola Urundai when we get bored without any good snacks at home😄

It's original recipe has roasted gram instead of nuts.I just recreated them.If you don't have any restrictions in adding them ,you can absolutely go by adding 1/4 cup of it while dry grinding the ingredients 

Also they are deep fried ones at home when we were kids.Better to go with appe pan & they don't need that much oil to get shallow fried 

Coconut acts as a very good binder.Dont add water to it.You will feel bit sticky when you roll them since we added some nuts .But never mind, Just add them to the pan & cook.Its done in minutes

Do try & let me know 🤗 Good day Everyone ☘️

Veg Series : Recipe 11

It's a very simple yet delicious protein rich Paneer Toast.
I just replaced bread with paneer, otherwise the fillings  absolutely can be your wish 

I was having some left over pan fried onions,so topped them along with some grated Cheese & it was a good combination the whole😋

Also I toasted the paneer with fried garlic butter.it can simply be plain butter or ghee.You can add on pepper powder or chilli flakes if you need some spice while mixing up the avocado.Hope you like it 🤗
